    VALUES (
      act_id, 'stem', 0, 'Robot Turn Instructions: Write step-by-step instructions for a floor robot to draw a right-angled triangle with sides 3 m, 4 m, and 5 m. Use only MOVE FORWARD, TURN RIGHT, TURN LEFT. Now check yourself: which angle in your plan did you have to guess rather than measure, and what extra piece of information would remove that guess?', 'Only one angle is fixed for certain by the 3-4-5 triangle -- which one, and why?',
      '{"answer_type": "short_text", "body": {"value": "A right-angled 3-4-5 triangle has one guaranteed 90-degree angle; the other two angles need measuring or calculating, not guessing -- exactly the precision a navigation app needs before giving turn-by-turn directions."}}'::jsonb,
      '{"grade": 6, "chapter_dependent": true, "external_id": "AIQ-MAT-030"}'::jsonb
